*********************************************************************

1. Moving Logic Into the Database
January 13, 2003
Do you find yourself demanding more precise control over your data? Join Tim
Perdue as he describes how to strip programming logic from the PHP code and move
it into the database itself.
http://www.databasejournal.com/features/php/article.php/1568461
------------------------------------------------------------

2. Leveraging the Information_schema
January 10, 2003
Checking for a particular string in every character column and user table in a
database is not an enviable task. Fortunately--it's not necessary. Discover
Information Schema, and learn how to get SQL Server to write the bulk of the SQL
with a bit of Dynamic SQL.
http://www.databasejournal.com/features/mssql/article.php/1567611
------------------------------------------------------------

3. SQL Server Stored Procedures Optimization Tips
January 8, 2003
In his latest article, Alexander Chigrik offers twelve useful tips for ensuring
that you've constructed your SQL Server stored procedures to perform in the most
efficient manner possible.
http://www.databasejournal.com/features/mssql/article.php/1565961
------------------------------------------------------------


